# NPM Scripts

## Testing

```bash
# Run tests
npm test

# Run tests in watch mode
npm run test.watch
```

## Code Quality

```bash
# Run ESLint
npm run eslint

# Run ESLint with auto-fix
npm run eslint.fix
```

## Coverage

```bash
# Run tests with coverage report
npm run coverage

# Check coverage meets thresholds (80% minimum)
npm run coverage.check

# Upload coverage to Codecov
npm run coverage.report
```

## Documentation

```bash
# Generate JSDoc documentation
npm run doc.generate
```

## Full Validation

```bash
# Run linting, tests, and coverage check
npm run validate
```

## Setup

```bash
# Install dependencies and run validation
npm run setup
```

## Mutation Testing

```bash
# Run Stryker mutation tests
npx stryker run
```

## Publishing

The project uses semantic-release for automated npm publishing.

```bash
# Test npm publish without actually publishing
npm publish --dry-run
```

## CI/CD Workflows

GitHub Actions workflows in `.github/workflows/`:

- `continuous-integration.yml` - Runs on push/PR to master
  - ESLint
  - Tests with coverage
  - Mutation testing
  - Codecov upload

- `release.yml` - Runs after CI passes on master
  - Semantic release to npm

- `runnable.yml` - Verifies package works
- `runnable-old-node.yml` - Tests on older Node.js versions
- `runnable-without-optional-dependencies.yml` - Tests without French/Russian dictionaries
